<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Ceratophyllum</i> <i>demersum</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the herbaceous layer with <i>Myriophyllum</i> spp. or <i>Polygonum</i> <i>amphibium</i>. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbaceous layer is open to continuous; submerged. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Slow-moving streams and rivers, ponds, lakes, and sloughs. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Ceratophyllum demersum</i>  as an OBL plant. </div>
</div>

		
